The paper deals with algorithms for matching problems in preference systems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and game theory (cs.DS and cs.GT). The use of preference lists and stable matching also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
